-- Telefonica to Bid for Costa Rica Mobile License, Economista Newspaper Says
-- Ben Sills
-- 2010-09-07T05:51:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-07/telefonica-to-bid-for-costa-rica-mobile-license-economista-newspaper-says.html

          
          
             Telefonica SA, Spain’s largest
telephone company, will bid for one of three mobile phone
license that the Costa Rican government is selling via auction,
El Economista reported.   
 America Movil SAB de CV, Millicom Internacional Cellular
SA, Cable & Wireless and Digicel Group Ltd. may also bid for the
right to operate in the market of 4.5 million people, the
newspaper added, without saying how it obtained the information.  
 El Economista didn’t say how much the companies may offer
for the licenses.    
